      "id": "task_1782768346_5544_81730",
      "title": "mixed-signal electrochemical biosensor front end driven by one-compartment oral pharmacokinetic concentration profile",
      "created_at": "2026-06-29 21:25:46",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-29 22:01:53",
      "status": "active",
      "stage": "teach",
      "summary": "Teaching plan ready. Probe or export evidence next.",
      "progress": 96,
      "prompt": "Build a Simscape teaching example for a pharmacokinetic drug concentration input driving an electrochemical biosensor front end. Use a one-compartment oral PK profile C(t) as the input signal, convert concentration to sensor current with sensitivity 25 nA/uM and first-order membrane mass-transfer lag tau_m = 4 s, then a transimpedance amplifier Rf = 1 MOhm with Cf = 10 nF and a 12-bit ADC. Probe concentration, sensor current, TIA output, and settling error. Teach PK input, mass-transfer lag, TIA bandwidth/noise tradeoff, and ADC saturation.",
