    {
      "id": "task_1782761708_1157_60198",
      "title": "simplified two-electrode voltage-clamp cell membrane with passive membrane, leak reversal potential, clamp amplifier, and series electrode resistance",
      "created_at": "2026-06-29 19:35:08",
      "updated_at": "2026-06-29 21:25:45",
      "status": "active",
      "stage": "probe",
      "summary": "Ready for teaching and probing.",
      "progress": 90,
      "prompt": "Build a Simscape teaching example for a two-electrode voltage-clamp cell membrane. Model the membrane as Cm = 100 pF in parallel with a leak conductance of 10 nS, with a resting reversal source near -70 mV. Drive a command step from -70 mV to -20 mV through a clamp amplifier and a 5 MOhm series electrode resistance. Probe membrane voltage, clamp current, and electrode voltage drop. Teach capacitive transient current, leak current, series-resistance clamp error, and why the probe reference node matters.\n",
